The paper deals with the theoretical analysis of compressive sensing, which is a topic that falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Signal Processing (cs.SP) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the design of a universal CS measurement, which involves subsampling and recovery of sparse signals, making it relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves mathematical analysis and optimization, which falls under the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-category.
